# UltraShape cleaning replica — environment variable configuration.
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` and edit to match your setup. The package
# itself does NOT auto-load ``.env`` (no python-dotenv dependency); the
# file is a **template** meant for you to source manually or export the
# values however your shell / launcher prefers, e.g.
#
#     export $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)
#
# All variables are optional. Helpers in
# ``ultrashape_cleaning/_config.py`` provide sensible defaults (HF hub
# id for the VLM, in-process execution for Stage 2, no VAE unless
# configured). Setting them is required only if you actually want to
# run the VAE / VLM / two-env split on a local cluster.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# UltraShape VAE (Stage 4 fragmentation check)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# YAML config for the VAE architecture (from the UltraShape repo).
# ULTRASHAPE_VAE_CONFIG=/path/to/UltraShape-1.0/configs/infer_dit_refine.yaml

# Combined checkpoint file containing the VAE weights under the "vae" key.
# ULTRASHAPE_VAE_CKPT=/path/to/ultrashape_v1.pt

# Root of the UltraShape repo (the directory containing the
# ``ultrashape`` python package). Only needed if the package is not
# already importable (``import ultrashape`` from an installed env
# makes this unnecessary).
# ULTRASHAPE_REPO_ROOT=/path/to/UltraShape-1.0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Qwen3-VL-8B (Stage 2 VLM filter, Stage 3 VLM canonicalization)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Directory of a local checkpoint, OR a HuggingFace hub id. Defaults to
# the hub id ``Qwen/Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct`` (HuggingFace will download
# the weights on first use if your HF cache is writable).
# QWEN3VL_MODEL_PATH=/path/to/Qwen3-VL-8B-Instruct

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Two-env split (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If your cubvh/torch env and your transformers-4.57/Qwen3-VL env are
# separate, point this at the second env's python interpreter. Stage 2
# will be invoked as a subprocess in that interpreter. When unset, Stage
# 2 runs in-process in the current interpreter (requires transformers
# >= 4.57 and torch >= 2.5 in the same env).
# VLM_PYTHON_EXE=/path/to/buildingseg/bin/python

# Working directory for the sidecar subprocess. Must contain the
# ``ultrashape_cleaning`` package on ``sys.path``. Defaults to the repo
# root (inferred from the installed package location).
# VLM_SIDECAR_CWD=/path/to/ultrashape-cleaning-replica

# CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES to propagate to the sidecar. Unset = inherit from
# the parent process.
# VLM_SIDECAR_CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HSSD / demo inputs (used only by scripts/run_demo.sh)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HSSD_DIR=/path/to/hssd/raw
